ENGL 4341 - Genre Studies in American Literature
Intensive study of one genre (poetry, novel, short story, or drama) in
American literature with an emphasis on the development of techniques,
forms, and styles. The course will include a variety of critical approaches
to the genre and will require extensive reading, research, and writing.
The course may be repeated once for credit when content changes.
Prerequisite: ENGL 3308, or permission of the instructor.
